cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use these prompts, please cite them as below."
title: "idta-smt-extraction-prompts"
abstract: >-
  Five SHA-pinned LLM prompts (v0–v4) for schema-aware constraint
  extraction from IDTA Submodel Template PDFs. Each version adds
  exactly one design feature on top of the previous (layout-aware
  reading, bounded template node graph, honesty contract, few-shot
  examples), making the v0→v4 series a controlled single-axis
  ablation. The prompts emit JSON arrays of typed constraint
  records with calibrated abstention via a closed status
  vocabulary. Headline F1 on IDTA 02006 Digital Nameplate v3.0.1
  with qwen2.5:7b-instruct at temperature 0.0: v2 F1=0.481 at
  precision 0.905, v3 precision 1.000 at F1=0.474. Within-prompt-
  SHA stability rate 1.000 across K=5 runs.
type: software
